        g: '05389000', avg: 280, histFlow: 252, mx: 530, my: 185, abbr: 'IA',
        desc: "Iowa's most remote paddling corridor flows through the 8,500-acre Yellow River State Forest — the largest contiguous forest in the state. Cold-water trout streams, rugged Driftless Area topography, and virtually no development create a wilderness experience unique in Iowa. The Paint Creek Unit offers the most secluded backcountry camping in the state.",
        desig: 'Yellow River State Forest · Iowa Coldwater Trout Stream',
